{"id":"1905.00239","submitter":"Jianguo Qian","authors":"Maoqun Wang and Jianguo Qian","title":"An Ore-type condition for existence of two disjoint cycles","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $n_{1}$ and $n_{2}$ be two integers with $n_{1},n_{2}\\geq3$ and $G$ a\ngraph of order $n=n_{1}+n_{2}$. As a generalization of Ore's degree condition\nfor the existence of Hamilton cycle in $G$, El-Zahar proved that if\n$\\delta(G)\\geq\n\\left\\lceil\\frac{n_{1}}{2}\\right\\rceil+\\left\\lceil\\frac{n_{2}}{2}\\right\\rceil$\nthen $G$ contains two disjoint cycles of length $n_{1}$ and $n_{2}$. Recently,\nYan et. al considered the problem by extending the degree condition to degree\nsum condition and proved that if $d(u)+d(v)\\geq n+4$ for any pair of\nnon-adjacent vertices $u$ and $v$ of $G$, then $G$ contains two disjoint cycles\nof length $n_{1}$ and $n_{2}$. They further asked whether the degree sum\ncondition can be improved to $d(u)+d(v)\\geq n+2$. In this paper, we give a\npositive answer to this question. Our result also generalizes El-Zahar's result\nwhen $n_{1}$ and $n_{2}$ are both odd.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 May 2019 09:52:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-02"}
